WEBVTT

00:01.702 --> 00:03.771
Right. I hope
everyone's hungry. Jimmy?

00:04.772 --> 00:07.241
Hey, Ray, you want a drumstick?
Go deep.

00:07.275 --> 00:08.476
Cut!

00:08.509 --> 00:10.644
Jimmy, if you don't respect
Thanksgiving rehearsal,

00:10.678 --> 00:12.012
what will you take
seriously?

00:12.046 --> 00:13.247
Mm. Nothing?

00:13.281 --> 00:15.483
Tomorrow is the first time
in five years

00:15.516 --> 00:17.151
that my mother
will have visited.

00:17.185 --> 00:18.686
I would like it
to go smoothly.

00:18.719 --> 00:21.189
Let's rehearse again.
Is everyone clear who they are?

00:21.222 --> 00:22.590
I'm me.
Me.
Me.

00:22.623 --> 00:24.725
Well, I'm three people --
and not at all troubled

00:24.758 --> 00:27.395
by the historical implications
of being assigned a value

00:27.428 --> 00:28.929
as a fraction
of a white person.

00:28.962 --> 00:30.864
Is that bad?
It's not great.

00:30.898 --> 00:33.000
Why can't Taylor
be Taylor?

00:33.033 --> 00:36.404
Because she alone has
the presence and regal bearing

00:36.437 --> 00:37.738
to approximate my mother.

00:37.771 --> 00:40.574
[ Bad Cockney accent ]
I'm your dear old mumsy, I am.

00:40.608 --> 00:42.443
Hey! We found something
Taylor can't do.

00:42.476 --> 00:44.678
Kenneth: Well, I'll miss
all the fun tomorrow.

00:44.712 --> 00:47.915
I signed up to have dinner
with my dad -- The Colonel.

00:47.948 --> 00:49.383
Don't get me started.
We won't.

00:49.417 --> 00:50.918
Jimmy, have you prepared
your toast?

00:50.951 --> 00:53.020
I sure have.
[ Clears throat ]

00:53.053 --> 00:56.424
I'd like to extend a warm
welcome to our honored guest.

00:56.457 --> 00:59.059
Andrea, you are withholding
and cold.

00:59.093 --> 01:00.528
Also, you're this genius

01:00.561 --> 01:03.063
who's been curing cancer
for 45 years,

01:03.097 --> 01:06.434
yet you and I have cured the
exact same number of cancers.

01:06.467 --> 01:09.203
Look, I get it. You don't
like it when she comes around.

01:09.237 --> 01:11.439
I just don't like how you turn
into a different person.

01:11.472 --> 01:13.441
Oh, I'd love to see that.
Well, you haven't heard
how I'm different.

01:13.474 --> 01:14.442
[ Laughs ]
Doesn't matter.

01:14.475 --> 01:16.610
She gets all nervous
and sweaty,

01:16.644 --> 01:18.546
and she starts apologizing
for stuff.

01:18.579 --> 01:19.780
It is nuts!

01:19.813 --> 01:22.383
Here's an idea -- instead of
looking for the approval

01:22.416 --> 01:24.452
that she has never
and will never give you,

01:24.485 --> 01:25.953
why not just be yourself?

01:25.986 --> 01:28.122
There's a lovely idea.
Now back to reality.

01:28.156 --> 01:30.891
My mother is extremely exacting,
and to that end,

01:30.924 --> 01:33.561
this time,
we will be prepared.

01:33.594 --> 01:36.764
Dylan, read up on the great
Chelsea Football Club.

01:36.797 --> 01:39.767
JJ, I've customized a board
with British witticisms.

01:39.800 --> 01:40.801
Learn it.

01:40.834 --> 01:42.970
And, Ray, please,
will you catch up

01:43.003 --> 01:45.606
on Mummy's favorite show,
"Wavendon Manor."

01:45.639 --> 01:47.508
It's like "Downton Abbey,"
but less fun.

01:47.541 --> 01:49.977
Great. That was my one complaint
about "Downton Abbey."

01:50.010 --> 01:52.680
I just want everyone to be
on their best behavior.

01:52.713 --> 01:54.848
And for God's sake,
whatever you do,

01:54.882 --> 01:57.451
don't mention
her arch medical rival,

01:57.485 --> 01:59.119
Ernst Bowman-Schrieber.

01:59.153 --> 02:01.322
"But we love him so."

02:01.355 --> 02:02.790
[ Laughs ]
Do you know what?

02:02.823 --> 02:04.858
Clear off, 'cause I got
more cleaning to do.

02:04.892 --> 02:06.360
Come on, Taylor.
You're up.

02:06.394 --> 02:08.529
[ Vacuum cleaner running ]

02:08.562 --> 02:10.531
-- Captions by VITAC --

02:10.564 --> 02:12.533
[ Turkey gobbles ]

02:12.566 --> 02:14.535
This is so much better
than sitting at home

02:14.568 --> 02:15.769
watching your mother
freak out.

02:15.803 --> 02:18.138
Hi. Give the kids
whatever they want.

02:18.172 --> 02:19.373
And I will have...

02:19.407 --> 02:21.375
Both:
The Godzilla Roll!

02:21.409 --> 02:24.044
What's the Godzilla Roll?

02:24.077 --> 02:25.279
"The biggest..." T-U

02:25.313 --> 02:28.449
"...tube of raw fish
ya ever done seen."

02:28.482 --> 02:30.684
Like a friggin'
Duraflame log.

02:30.718 --> 02:32.353
200 bucks a pop.

02:32.386 --> 02:33.321
[ Chuckles ]

02:33.354 --> 02:35.356
Oh. That's awful.

02:35.389 --> 02:36.524
And...so fast.

02:36.557 --> 02:37.791
Already made.

02:37.825 --> 02:40.294
They just sit there for days
daring you to order them.

02:40.328 --> 02:42.296
And if you finish it
within an hour,

02:42.330 --> 02:43.697
the whole table eats free.

02:43.731 --> 02:47.301
Which isn't a problem, because
Dad is a legendary power-eater.

02:47.335 --> 02:48.636
Please. I'm no hero.

02:48.669 --> 02:50.304
I'm just a gross poor guy

02:50.338 --> 02:52.973
who doesn't care
what he puts into his body.

02:53.006 --> 02:54.508
[ Ticking ]
Thank you.

02:54.542 --> 02:56.377
Let the games begin.

02:56.410 --> 02:59.313
**

02:59.347 --> 03:01.315
Dad, are you okay?
I'm fine.

03:01.349 --> 03:03.584
Why don't you guys go ahead
to the ice cream place?

03:03.617 --> 03:05.253
I'll catch up.
Order me the Belly Buster.

03:08.289 --> 03:09.690
Isn't he gross?

03:09.723 --> 03:11.459
[ Ticking continues ]

03:12.726 --> 03:13.894
I can't do it.
I'm sorry.

03:13.927 --> 03:15.729
I know we're kind of
all in this together

03:15.763 --> 03:17.365
and you guys are rooting
for me.

03:17.398 --> 03:19.199
[ Timer dings ]
He didn't finish it!

03:19.233 --> 03:20.768
[ Cheering, laughter ]

03:20.801 --> 03:22.903
All right.
You think that's funny?

03:22.936 --> 03:24.405
Wait till you try
and run this.

03:24.438 --> 03:26.274
Maya: Okay, people,
this is not a drill.

03:26.307 --> 03:28.842
It's here --
Thanksgiving.

03:28.876 --> 03:30.344
Mummy will be here
in a second.

03:30.378 --> 03:31.512
[ Sighs ]

03:31.545 --> 03:33.414
Jimmy, what's wrong?
You've been down all day.

03:33.447 --> 03:35.883
Did the UPS guy call you
"ma'am" again?
If only.

03:35.916 --> 03:37.351
Is this because you couldn't
finish the Godzilla Roll?

03:37.385 --> 03:40.087
Shh! The kids
don't know about that.

03:40.120 --> 03:42.022
Didn't you just vacuum?

03:42.055 --> 03:43.691
Oh! Kids.
Is everyone ready?

03:43.724 --> 03:45.025
Dylan, how's
the football watching going?

03:45.058 --> 03:47.060
Couldn't do it.
I watched two seconds.

03:47.094 --> 03:49.697
Soccer sucks so hard
that I read a book.

03:49.730 --> 03:50.464
Dylan!

03:50.498 --> 03:52.266
JJ, how's the British lingo?

03:52.300 --> 03:53.133
"Blimey."

03:53.166 --> 03:54.735
That doesn't make
any sense.

03:54.768 --> 03:56.370
Didn't you study at all?

03:56.404 --> 03:57.438
"The tube."

03:57.471 --> 03:59.039
[ Sighs ]
Ray, please tell me

03:59.072 --> 04:00.474
you've been watching
"Wavendon Manor."

04:00.508 --> 04:03.877
Have I? The legal proceedings
the family's going through?

04:03.911 --> 04:04.978
It's so dry!

04:05.012 --> 04:05.946
Excellent.

04:05.979 --> 04:07.114
Well, you're in charge

04:07.147 --> 04:08.649
of getting these two twits
up to speed.

04:08.682 --> 04:09.650
Yes!

04:09.683 --> 04:11.151
Looks like
I call the shots now.

04:11.184 --> 04:12.553
Oh!
Unhand your superior!

04:12.586 --> 04:14.688
[ Knock on door ]
She's here. She's here!

04:15.756 --> 04:16.824
It's just Billy!

04:16.857 --> 04:19.660
Harsh!
And on this holiest of days.

04:19.693 --> 04:21.462
Where are
Audrey and the kids?

04:21.495 --> 04:23.331
They're not coming.
They got a nasty stomach bug.

04:23.364 --> 04:24.998
I'll spare you the gory details,
but let's just say

04:25.032 --> 04:27.401
they would not be allowed
in a hotel pool.

04:27.435 --> 04:29.169
As per the sign.

04:29.202 --> 04:30.571
Regarding active viruses.

04:30.604 --> 04:32.506
Yeah, I quite understand.
Yeah.

04:32.540 --> 04:33.707
Hey, Billy.

04:35.142 --> 04:36.276
Oh, he's been upset
all day.

04:36.310 --> 04:37.945
Hey. Hey.
[ Grumbles ]

04:37.978 --> 04:39.680
Billy's here.
Talk to me, pal.

04:39.713 --> 04:40.948
I-I...

04:40.981 --> 04:42.950
I couldn't finish
the Godzilla Roll yesterday.

04:42.983 --> 04:46.086
Oh, no, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no.
No-no-no-no-no-no-
no-no-no-no-no-no.

04:46.119 --> 04:47.120
Jimmy.
[ Knock on door ]

04:47.154 --> 04:49.189
[ Gasps ] She's here!
Go on, get out! Get!

04:50.691 --> 04:51.725
Mummy.

04:52.560 --> 04:53.927
Oh. Hello, Taylor.

04:53.961 --> 04:55.028
And you must be...

04:55.062 --> 04:57.097
Hi, Mrs. DiMeo.
This is my brother, Logan.

04:57.130 --> 04:58.198
I know it's last-minute,

04:58.231 --> 05:00.033
but would it be okay
if he joined us?

05:00.067 --> 05:01.435
Sure. It's fine.

05:01.469 --> 05:03.471
JJ will be happy to see
one of his friends from camp.

05:05.906 --> 05:09.477
[ Western showdown music plays ]

05:09.510 --> 05:10.711
Ray: "You."

05:10.744 --> 05:12.346
Hello.

05:12.380 --> 05:14.214
[ Music intensifies ]
"Goodbye."

05:14.247 --> 05:16.517
[ Music stops ]
Nope. No time
for this mysterious feud.

05:16.550 --> 05:18.318
[ Knock on door ]
[ Gasps ] Mummy's here!

05:18.352 --> 05:19.319
Go on. Off you go.

05:19.353 --> 05:20.788
Go to your room.
Go to your room.

05:20.821 --> 05:22.690
Peace and calm.

05:23.657 --> 05:24.892
I hate my dad!

05:24.925 --> 05:27.828
That sounds terrible
and not at all my problem!

05:27.861 --> 05:29.229
Oh, Lord!

05:29.262 --> 05:32.232
I'm sweating straight through my
convincing knock-off Burberry.

05:32.265 --> 05:33.534
[ Knock on door ]

05:35.168 --> 05:36.437
Ohh!

05:38.105 --> 05:39.072
Where's Kenneth?!

05:39.106 --> 05:40.708
He's in the kitchen,
whoever you are!

05:40.741 --> 05:42.676
I'm the Colonel!
Lead me to him!

05:42.710 --> 05:45.045
Kenneth: He found me?!
Follow me!

05:45.078 --> 05:47.548
[ Military march plays ]

05:49.182 --> 05:51.385
[ Knock on door ]
Kenneth: How in the world
did you find me?!

05:51.419 --> 05:52.586
Colonel:
I got my ways!

05:52.620 --> 05:54.755
Steady. Steady.

05:54.788 --> 05:56.323
Oh! No!

05:56.356 --> 05:57.324
Oh! [ Gasps ]

05:57.357 --> 05:59.593
Stupid Taylor cord!!

05:59.627 --> 06:01.028
[ Sighs ]

06:01.061 --> 06:02.563
All right. All right.

06:02.596 --> 06:04.097
It's all right.
She'll never know.

06:04.131 --> 06:05.399
All right.

06:06.867 --> 06:08.469
Hurry!
She'll be here soon!

06:12.239 --> 06:14.875
Maya: I'll be right there,
Mummy! Hold on!

06:14.908 --> 06:16.410
Oh, hello. Ohh.

06:16.444 --> 06:17.878
Ah, so sorry.

06:17.911 --> 06:20.180
Uh, how was your flight in?
Was it good?

06:20.213 --> 06:22.516
Well? Good? What?

06:22.550 --> 06:25.385
I'm sorry. I'm just
very excited to see you.

06:25.419 --> 06:28.556
Would you like
a delicious, fresh parfait?

06:28.589 --> 06:30.290
That would be delightful.

06:30.323 --> 06:31.925
I don't have
one of those.

06:32.826 --> 06:34.428
How's
Ernst Bowman-Schrieber?

06:34.462 --> 06:36.597
Ugh!
Why did you...

06:37.565 --> 06:41.201
I mean, more broadly,
how's your research?

06:41.234 --> 06:43.604
I'm in the twilight
of my career

06:43.637 --> 06:46.574
after decades
of frustrating lab trials.

06:46.607 --> 06:47.808
No cure in sight,

06:47.841 --> 06:49.977
but you can't say I didn't kill
a hell of a lot of rats.

06:50.010 --> 06:51.378
Excellent.

06:51.411 --> 06:53.380
Kenneth: Just take
some dry turkey and leave!
I --

06:53.413 --> 06:55.449
Colonel:
Even your yelling is off-key!
So sorry. Uh...is there anything
I can get you, really?

06:55.483 --> 06:56.450
Anything at all?

06:56.484 --> 06:58.719
Two yelling strangers
would be nice.

06:58.752 --> 07:00.954
Oh. Absolutely right.
Sorry. I'm just --

07:00.988 --> 07:02.556
Unacceptable.

07:02.590 --> 07:03.824
I am
listening to you --

07:03.857 --> 07:05.826
Whatever this is,
take it somewhere else!

07:05.859 --> 07:07.060
Look,
I am not leaving here

07:07.094 --> 07:08.562
until my son
shows me some respect.

07:08.596 --> 07:10.130
Well, I hope you like
dry-ass turkey,

07:10.163 --> 07:11.632
'cause we're gonna be here
a while!

07:11.665 --> 07:13.133
Sorry, Maya.
Your sides are good.

07:13.166 --> 07:14.334
Listen!

07:14.367 --> 07:16.136
I understand that respect
is very important to you.

07:16.169 --> 07:18.005
I, for one,
appreciate your service.

07:18.038 --> 07:19.640
My service?
What's she mean?

07:19.673 --> 07:21.475
She thinks you're in the Army,
Colonel.

07:21.509 --> 07:23.243
You never heard
of a stage name before?

07:23.276 --> 07:25.012
You do know The Beatles
aren't bugs, right?

07:25.045 --> 07:26.013
[ Laughs ]

07:26.046 --> 07:28.616
I hate him,
but he got you.

07:28.649 --> 07:29.850
I'm no soldier.
I'm a singer.

07:29.883 --> 07:31.451
We used to have an act
when he was young.

07:31.485 --> 07:33.186
It was called "The Colonel
and Little Kenny."

07:33.220 --> 07:34.922
What?
You know, weddings,
hotel bars.

07:34.955 --> 07:36.790
You ever been to the Holiday Inn
in Troy, New York?

07:36.824 --> 07:38.358
No.
Well, neither has he!

07:38.391 --> 07:39.660
Quit before the big gig.

07:39.693 --> 07:42.462
I had to sing both sides
of "I Got You Babe" to myself.

07:42.496 --> 07:44.131
Now, would you pay
to see that?

07:44.164 --> 07:45.165
Holiday Inn didn't.

07:45.198 --> 07:47.100
Well, I'd had enough
of you riding me.

07:47.134 --> 07:49.637
"Kenneth, you're sharp.
Kenneth, you're pitchy.

07:49.670 --> 07:51.705
Kenneth, slouch
so I'm taller than you."

07:51.739 --> 07:54.374
I'm taller than you, Dad!
I just am!

07:54.407 --> 07:55.709
Will you stop it?!

07:55.743 --> 07:58.078
I will not have you ruin my day
or my turkey!

07:59.747 --> 08:00.781
Oh --
Maybe you should --

08:00.814 --> 08:02.049
I'm basting it!

08:02.082 --> 08:06.453
So, you were unable to eat
a 10-pound sushi roll,

08:06.486 --> 08:07.688
and that's bad?

08:07.721 --> 08:09.957
It just means
I'm not what I once was.

08:09.990 --> 08:13.193
Was there ever a recognition
you got in your younger days?

08:13.226 --> 08:14.895
Yes, that helps me
to understand.

08:14.928 --> 08:16.296
Yes, at 31,

08:16.329 --> 08:18.365
I was the youngest-ever
recipient of the Copley Award.

08:18.398 --> 08:20.000
Okay.
And you never won it again?

08:20.033 --> 08:23.336
I won it five more times,
but I was never able to eat it.

08:23.370 --> 08:25.539
You should have seen this guy
in his prime.

08:25.573 --> 08:27.975
Billy.
So, once
when we were kids,

08:28.008 --> 08:29.543
I left him alone
in my room.

08:29.577 --> 08:32.045
Came back,
all my action figures -- gone.

08:32.079 --> 08:35.048
[ Laughs ] This guy was
pooping G.I. Joes for weeks!

08:35.082 --> 08:36.083
No, no. Billy, stop!

08:36.116 --> 08:37.517
So sorry, Mummy.
He's a dentist.

08:37.551 --> 08:39.820
He's used to telling stories
to people who can't get away.

08:39.853 --> 08:41.822
He wants to drag me out
to cheer me up.

08:41.855 --> 08:45.058
I want to make sure
you and your mom have
the best day possible.

08:45.092 --> 08:47.761
Me too. Take him.
Yes!
Come on, come on!

08:47.795 --> 08:50.197
Be back in time
for G.I. Joes!

08:50.230 --> 08:52.700
So sorry, Mummy.
[ Kenneth and Colonel arguing ]

08:52.733 --> 08:54.034
Mm. I -- you --

08:54.067 --> 08:55.235
I shan't be a second.

08:55.268 --> 08:56.503
Just relax.

08:56.536 --> 08:58.338
All right, JJ,
how's your British lingo?

08:58.371 --> 09:00.841
Do you know
what a plonker is?

09:00.874 --> 09:03.677
No! No cultivating
this weird rivalry!

09:03.711 --> 09:05.746
And, Dylan,
time to study up on soccer.

09:05.779 --> 09:06.980
I made you flash cards.

09:09.216 --> 09:11.451
[ Window closes ]
You two should be ashamed.

09:11.484 --> 09:13.553
The pilgrims came here
to get away from soccer.

09:13.587 --> 09:14.955
Right.
Well, for Grandma's sake,

09:14.988 --> 09:17.024
let's be more British
and less American.

09:17.057 --> 09:18.358
Less American?

09:18.391 --> 09:19.526
It's just for the day.

09:19.559 --> 09:21.394
You don't turn off
being American.

09:21.428 --> 09:23.931
There ain't no switch on
the Statue of Liberty's torch!

09:25.432 --> 09:27.367
"Yeah, you...

09:27.400 --> 09:28.468
Brexit."

09:28.501 --> 09:30.270
That's not
how you use that word!

09:30.303 --> 09:32.806
Mom? Mom,
they aren't listening to me!

09:32.840 --> 09:34.775
May I have
spanking powers?

09:34.808 --> 09:36.443
Oh, hello, Grandmother.

09:36.476 --> 09:37.611
Hello, Raymond.

09:37.645 --> 09:39.913
Nobody calls me that,
and I love it so much.

09:40.648 --> 09:42.950
Oh. Let me
introduce you to, uh --

09:42.983 --> 09:44.117
[ Laughing ] Introduce?

09:44.151 --> 09:46.119
It hasn't been
that long.

09:46.153 --> 09:48.288
Hello, Dylan.
Mmm!

09:48.321 --> 09:51.759
And JJ -- lady-killer!

09:51.792 --> 09:53.961
Pictures don't
do you justice.

09:53.994 --> 09:55.796
Nope. Nope.
But -- But that's him.

09:55.829 --> 09:59.299
Uh --
Don't forget, JJ --
you can't speak.

09:59.332 --> 10:01.935
Excuse me, but I'd like
to go freshen up.

10:01.969 --> 10:03.637
Bathroom's back
and to the right.

10:03.671 --> 10:06.974
I'll just be here
with JJ and Dylan.

10:07.007 --> 10:08.909
All right, I know it's weird,
but my job is

10:08.942 --> 10:11.144
to get those two presentable,
and I can't do that.

10:11.178 --> 10:12.579
Will you be
JJ and Dylan?

10:12.612 --> 10:13.681
Will JJ be upset?

10:13.714 --> 10:14.848
Probably.
I'm in.

10:14.882 --> 10:17.918
I don't like it,
but I'll do anything for you.

10:17.951 --> 10:19.152
You need to work
on your Dylan.

10:19.186 --> 10:21.354
Where are
Dylan and JJ?

10:21.388 --> 10:22.222
Here.

10:23.456 --> 10:25.592
The other two just weren't
gonna get there. I --

10:25.625 --> 10:27.861
Grandma thought these two
were them, so I made a call.

10:29.897 --> 10:31.331
Right. Go and tell the other two
they're out.

10:32.299 --> 10:34.434
Okay, so,
I talked to Mom.

10:34.467 --> 10:37.070
You guys are no longer
JJ and Dylan.

10:38.138 --> 10:39.873
You guys
will stay in here and --

10:39.907 --> 10:41.208
"Away from Logan?

10:41.241 --> 10:42.542
I'm in."

10:42.575 --> 10:44.177
If I have to be British
out there,

10:44.211 --> 10:45.713
then here
is where I'll stay.

10:48.181 --> 10:50.550
[ "The Star-Spangled Banner"
plays ]

10:54.254 --> 10:56.289
Jimmy: So, when did you, uh,
get this thing?

10:56.323 --> 10:58.658
This is a trial-separation gift
to myself.

10:59.426 --> 11:00.894
Yeah, I lied.

11:00.928 --> 11:02.963
Audrey left me.
She doesn't have the flu.

11:02.996 --> 11:05.198
She might have the flu.
I don't know.

11:05.232 --> 11:06.466
But I'm fine.

11:06.499 --> 11:08.802
There's this 26-year-old
hygienist in my office --

11:08.836 --> 11:10.537
complimented my socks
on Monday,

11:10.570 --> 11:13.373
so we can all see
the direction that's headed.

11:13.406 --> 11:16.043
Yeah. You're down about
the Godzilla Roll thing?

11:16.076 --> 11:18.678
Yeah, I get it -- feel like
you're missing a step.

11:18.712 --> 11:21.681
Well, I'm just the guy
to pull you out.

11:23.583 --> 11:25.819
**

11:25.853 --> 11:27.855
This...

11:27.888 --> 11:29.723
calls for hair.

11:29.757 --> 11:31.091
Ohhh!

11:31.124 --> 11:33.660
You never
walk out on a show!

11:33.693 --> 11:34.828
Enough bickering!

11:34.862 --> 11:36.363
What can I do
to get you two to stop?

11:36.396 --> 11:38.698
We wouldn't be bickering
at all if he...

11:38.732 --> 11:40.433
* Didn't go
breaking my heart *

11:40.467 --> 11:41.434
[ Snapping fingers ]

11:41.468 --> 11:43.036
Pitchy.

11:43.070 --> 11:44.404
Actually,
that was beautiful.

11:44.437 --> 11:47.274
Colonel, would you do my kitchen
the honor of a full song?

11:47.307 --> 11:49.242
Oh, I never turn down
a gig.

11:50.110 --> 11:53.113
* Don't go
breaking my heart *

11:53.146 --> 11:54.547
I think the next line
calls for Little Kenny?

11:54.581 --> 11:56.716
And I believe your green beans
need some salt,

11:56.750 --> 11:58.351
but I mind
my own damn business!

11:58.385 --> 11:59.452
Ah, suit yourself.

11:59.486 --> 12:02.222
* I couldn't if I tried

12:02.255 --> 12:06.126
* Oh, honey,
if I get restless *

12:06.159 --> 12:08.561
* Baby,
you're not that kind *

12:08.595 --> 12:11.098
* Do, do, do,
do, do, do *

12:11.131 --> 12:12.565
Yeah!
Oh, please!

12:12.599 --> 12:13.733
Well,
like you could do better?

12:13.767 --> 12:15.402
[ Scoffs ]
With my eyes closed!

12:16.403 --> 12:17.570
Wait a minute.

12:18.906 --> 12:20.540
I have that song
on my phone.

12:20.573 --> 12:22.810
[ "Don't Go Breaking My Heart"
plays ]

12:22.843 --> 12:26.613
* Don't go
breaking my heart *

12:26.646 --> 12:30.250
* You take the weight
off of me *

12:30.283 --> 12:34.221
* Oh, honey,
when you knock on my door *

12:34.254 --> 12:36.589
* I gave you my key

12:36.623 --> 12:38.125
In your face, Maya.

12:38.158 --> 12:39.259
* Ooh, ooh

12:39.292 --> 12:41.428
Well, thanks
for taking me out.

12:41.461 --> 12:43.263
[ Bottles clink ]
Yeah.
Best Thanksgiving ever.

12:43.296 --> 12:45.232
[ Laughs ]

12:45.265 --> 12:47.167
Whoa.
This is so perfect.

12:47.200 --> 12:49.002
You want to recapture
your youth?

12:49.036 --> 12:50.637
You can do it
as my wingman.

12:50.670 --> 12:52.840
She is so loving me!

12:52.873 --> 12:55.442
Found wig,
you've done it again.

12:55.475 --> 12:57.744
[ Clears throat ]

12:57.777 --> 13:00.013
Uh, my roommate and I

13:00.047 --> 13:03.283
are graduate students
at the nearby university,

13:03.316 --> 13:04.918
and, uh, we were wondering
if you --

13:04.952 --> 13:06.286
Please stop.

13:06.319 --> 13:08.088
[ Chuckles ] What?
Don't sell past the sale, right?

13:08.121 --> 13:09.289
I have a boyfriend.

13:09.322 --> 13:11.424
And I got a math test --
long as we're naming things

13:11.458 --> 13:12.926
we're gonna be
cheating on later.

13:12.960 --> 13:14.627
I said,
get out of my face!

13:14.661 --> 13:15.662
Jimmy: Whoa!

13:15.695 --> 13:16.763
Sorry. W-We --

13:16.796 --> 13:18.598
Ohh! Aaaah!

13:18.631 --> 13:20.167
Learn to spot an ally!

13:20.200 --> 13:23.270
Okay. Well, my buddy and I
are gonna head back to...

13:23.303 --> 13:24.271
the dorm.

13:24.304 --> 13:25.438
Happy Thanksgiving.

13:25.472 --> 13:27.841
[ Chuckling ]
Sorry that got so weird!

13:27.875 --> 13:29.442
No,
that actually helped.

13:29.476 --> 13:30.777
Maybe I have lost a step,

13:30.810 --> 13:34.781
but this is what losing a step
and not accepting it looks like.

13:34.814 --> 13:36.683
I got a family back home
who loves me.

13:36.716 --> 13:38.018
I should be there
with them

13:38.051 --> 13:40.153
instead of here,
getting punched.

13:41.188 --> 13:42.522
Then my little plan
worked.

13:42.555 --> 13:43.656
Wasn't your plan.

13:44.591 --> 13:47.194
Maya, I'm not an expert
on Thanksgiving dinner,

13:47.227 --> 13:48.896
but is there a dinner?

13:48.929 --> 13:50.663
Oh! Yes, of course.

13:50.697 --> 13:52.032
No, it should be dry
by now.

13:52.065 --> 13:53.200
Ready. Moist.

13:53.233 --> 13:55.502
Ooh. Don't over-promise.
Ready.

13:55.535 --> 13:56.403
Kids, dinner!

13:56.436 --> 13:58.071
Let's sit down,
shall we?

13:58.105 --> 14:00.307
Oh, Mummy, this is Kenneth
and his father.

14:00.340 --> 14:02.009
Ah, yes.
How nice to put a face

14:02.042 --> 14:03.877
to the, "Die, you old fool!
Die!"

14:03.911 --> 14:05.545
[ Laughs ]
They're just leaving.

14:05.578 --> 14:07.080
But the singing
makes me hungry.

14:07.114 --> 14:08.481
[ Chuckling ]
Like everything else.

14:08.515 --> 14:10.417
[ Laughs ]
I love this guy now.

14:10.450 --> 14:12.319
[ Chairs slide ]

14:12.352 --> 14:13.921
JJ, here.

14:13.954 --> 14:15.788
Dylan, you sit here.

14:17.891 --> 14:19.159
That's not
JJ and Dylan.

14:19.192 --> 14:21.028
Oh, isn't it?

14:22.262 --> 14:24.764
I'll play along,
but that's not hard.

14:24.797 --> 14:25.933
[ Grunts ]
Jimmy isn't back yet,

14:25.966 --> 14:27.667
so why don't we
go around the table

14:27.700 --> 14:29.236
and say
what we're thankful for.

14:29.269 --> 14:31.571
I'm thankful
that Conte finally realizes

14:31.604 --> 14:33.006
what he has in Batshuayi.

14:33.040 --> 14:34.674
He's Chelsea's best striker.

14:34.707 --> 14:37.710
Look at that! You are
most certainly my granddaughter.

14:37.744 --> 14:41.248
Wow. I could listen to you
talk about football all night.

14:41.281 --> 14:42.515
Sister!

14:42.549 --> 14:44.384
I'm thankful
my daddy and I are...

14:44.417 --> 14:46.119
Both: * Reunited

14:46.153 --> 14:49.589
* And it feels so good

14:49.622 --> 14:51.124
* Reunited

14:51.158 --> 14:53.760
* Where the hell's
the food? *

14:53.793 --> 14:54.962
Would you please?!

14:54.995 --> 14:55.963
Ohh! Ohh!

14:55.996 --> 14:57.897
Oh! Mummy!
Oh, I'm so sorry!

14:57.931 --> 14:59.566
I'm just a bit on edge.
I just --

14:59.599 --> 15:02.302
I-I know how you --
you like things just so.

15:02.335 --> 15:03.736
So this is on me?!

15:03.770 --> 15:05.805
I'm responsible
for all this madness?

15:05.838 --> 15:07.607
The singing, the shouting,

15:07.640 --> 15:09.542
the quite obvious
sexual chemistry

15:09.576 --> 15:11.311
between your daughter
and son?

15:11.344 --> 15:14.214
You're playing footsie with me,
young man!

15:14.247 --> 15:17.150
It's just so vulgar.

15:17.184 --> 15:19.152
So...American!

15:19.186 --> 15:21.488
Damn right it is,
toots.

15:21.521 --> 15:22.555
Who are you?

15:22.589 --> 15:24.257
Just a red-blooded,
chicken-fried,

15:24.291 --> 15:27.127
supersize
U.S. of A-merican.

15:27.160 --> 15:28.161
You feel me, tea bag?

15:28.195 --> 15:29.596
You're in America.

15:29.629 --> 15:31.131
In America,
we don't drink tea.

15:31.164 --> 15:32.632
We drink soda.

15:32.665 --> 15:34.467
[ Bottle cap fizzes ]

15:34.501 --> 15:37.004
[ "The Star-Spangled Banner"
plays ]

15:37.037 --> 15:38.171
Darling, no!

15:38.205 --> 15:41.708
[ Music continues ]

15:46.279 --> 15:47.847
[ Gasps ]

15:47.880 --> 15:49.582
Look what you made me do.

15:49.616 --> 15:51.484
She finished it.

15:51.518 --> 15:52.752
She has the gift.

15:52.785 --> 15:54.087
Weren't you bald?

15:54.121 --> 15:55.588
I don't know.
Was I?

15:55.622 --> 15:56.990
[ Sighs ]

15:57.024 --> 15:58.625
I raised you in a home.

15:58.658 --> 16:00.193
This is a circus!

16:00.227 --> 16:01.361
Enough!

16:01.394 --> 16:04.131
Your daughter ties herself
into knots for you.

16:04.164 --> 16:05.132
Jimmy,
you don't have to.

16:05.165 --> 16:06.933
No. I don't mind.
She can't hurt me.

16:06.966 --> 16:08.601
You couldn't eat
the Godzilla Roll.

16:08.635 --> 16:10.370
Ohh! Yes, she can.
[ Groans ]

16:10.403 --> 16:12.472
Happy Thanksgiving,
everyone.

16:13.640 --> 16:16.676
It's okay, Dad.
We still believe in you.

16:22.082 --> 16:23.683
[ Sighs ] I'm sorry.
That did not help.

16:23.716 --> 16:25.818
But someone
had to stand up to her.

16:25.852 --> 16:27.687
Yeah, I think
that somebody's me.

16:27.720 --> 16:30.023
I'm tired of trying to be
someone I'm not.

16:30.057 --> 16:32.392
And asking you
to be someone you're not

16:32.425 --> 16:34.894
And...having some of you
played by other people.

16:34.927 --> 16:37.530
Then go say it.
Be true to who you are.

16:37.564 --> 16:39.466
Did you lie
about the Godzilla Roll?

16:39.499 --> 16:40.967
Be true
if it feels right.

16:41.000 --> 16:43.103
It's not, like a, you know,
law or anything.

16:44.204 --> 16:45.505
Kenneth
overcooked the turkey.

16:45.538 --> 16:46.739
[ Door opens ]

16:46.773 --> 16:48.175
So, you lied?

16:48.208 --> 16:50.243
Hey, your dad took a punch
protecting me

16:50.277 --> 16:51.944
from a horny co-ed today,
so...

16:53.713 --> 16:54.747
Yeah, I lied.

16:54.781 --> 16:56.749
[ Sighs ]
I can't do it anymore.

16:56.783 --> 16:59.486
And you know what?
I have made peace with that.

16:59.519 --> 17:01.721
I don't have to prove anything
to myself.

17:01.754 --> 17:04.057
"Don't say
you can't do it."

17:04.091 --> 17:05.792
You can do anything.

17:06.793 --> 17:08.428
...gross.

17:08.461 --> 17:09.862
Jimmy, as someone

17:09.896 --> 17:13.666
who's had the admiration
of his child and lost it,

17:13.700 --> 17:15.668
I'll tell you --

17:15.702 --> 17:19.172
hold on to it
for as long as you can.

17:19.206 --> 17:21.040
Eat that Godzilla Roll.

17:21.074 --> 17:22.275
For them.

17:25.278 --> 17:26.579
Who are you?

17:26.613 --> 17:29.382
So, can we go to sushi now
or what?

17:29.416 --> 17:30.517
Yeah,
we're going to sushi.

17:30.550 --> 17:32.419
U.S.A.!

17:32.452 --> 17:34.020
All: U.S.A.!

17:34.053 --> 17:35.955
Well, I guess
I better be on my way.

17:35.988 --> 17:38.691
I got a gig at a card club
in Gardena.

17:38.725 --> 17:40.527
On Thanksgiving Day?
Oh, yeah.

17:40.560 --> 17:42.295
I turn "Ooh Baby Baby"
into --

17:42.329 --> 17:43.396
"Ooh Gravy Gravy."

17:43.430 --> 17:45.198
I've been doing
"Ooh Turkey Turkey,"

17:45.232 --> 17:46.799
but that's
a whole lot better.

17:46.833 --> 17:47.934
It's better, right?
Yeah, man!

17:47.967 --> 17:48.968
[ Both laugh ]

17:49.001 --> 17:50.303
[ Knock on door ]

17:51.971 --> 17:52.939
Maya --

17:52.972 --> 17:55.642
I'm coming in! Move.
I --

17:55.675 --> 17:57.144
Sit down.

17:57.177 --> 17:58.711
Oh, my God.
It worked.

17:58.745 --> 17:59.812
Quit while I'm ahead?

17:59.846 --> 18:01.381
No.
It's time to be honest.

18:01.414 --> 18:04.417
Mummy, on the rare occasions
that you come to visit,

18:04.451 --> 18:07.754
I always try to be
the daughter that you want --

18:07.787 --> 18:10.490
the fawning,
the Burberry.

18:10.523 --> 18:12.159
Are we being
entirely honest now?

18:12.192 --> 18:13.960
It's pretty bloody close!

18:13.993 --> 18:14.994
Look.

18:15.027 --> 18:17.297
My family isn't proper.

18:17.330 --> 18:19.232
We're loud and messy.

18:19.266 --> 18:22.302
What you saw today there,
that's who we are.

18:22.335 --> 18:24.003
I like us.

18:24.036 --> 18:26.673
And I think if you knew us,
you would, too.

18:26.706 --> 18:28.441
[ Sighs ]

18:28.475 --> 18:31.678
Maya, I've never been
very good at this.

18:31.711 --> 18:34.080
Work always came first.

18:34.113 --> 18:36.916
Family, feelings...

18:36.949 --> 18:39.486
I'm sorry.

18:39.519 --> 18:41.354
I'm not
who you need me to be.

18:41.388 --> 18:44.691
Well, we could work on this.
We could make this better.

18:45.992 --> 18:47.327
We could.

18:50.997 --> 18:52.031
Okay.

18:55.902 --> 18:57.170
I don't understand.

18:57.204 --> 18:58.771
Why did you want to come?

18:58.805 --> 19:01.174
I wanted to try.

19:01.208 --> 19:02.975
It's all I know.

19:03.009 --> 19:06.846
An experiment fails,
you get up the next day,

19:06.879 --> 19:08.781
you kill more rats.

19:08.815 --> 19:13.320
Also, your husband was
rather insistent that I come.

19:13.353 --> 19:16.789
[ "My Girl" plays ]

19:16.823 --> 19:18.725
Happy Thanksgiving,
Mummy.

19:18.758 --> 19:21.160
